On Fri, 15 Feb 2002, Greg Potts wrote:

> I have swapped a tank without removing the engine, but I had to pull the

> anyway. I can't imagine that you could swap a sender unit without pulling
> the tank or cutting a hole, there just isn't room. Disassembling FI just to
> avoid an engine drop wouldn't be worth it.

if you have thin hands (or someone you can con into helping) it is  very
possible to pull it and replace it, done it twice in my 78.

and you don't need to remove the FI, just the air intake (air cleaner, S
tube, Air Flow meter)  two screws and one plug.


it is a real contortionist operation but possible

